        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Thanks for the pointer, I was able to attach my local `nvim` to a remote instance in container using `nvim --listen 0.0.0.0:12345` and operate it from my machine with `nvim --remote-ui --server 0.0.0.0:12345` without the plugin. \r\n\r\nHowever, this is not what I'm looking for. The result is that I can connect to the _bare-bones_  `nvim` instance in the container, and the expected result is that I can edit files in the container from my local `nvim` instance. Running the command from within `nvim` terminal or without the `--remote-ui` flag doesn't work.\r\n\r\nA possible workaround could be `scp`, but it's tedious and allows only one file at a time. Am I missing something here?\r\n\r\nEDIT:\r\nAfter some digging, I found [this plugin](https://github.com/NOSDuco/remote-sshfs.nvim) to work for my use case, but still exploring.",
